      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">In a system where the units work in parallel, the parallel
communication shares the status and operation mode of each unit with
the other units. The system will:</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Try to operate both units in the highest priority operation
mode.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Try to operate both units in the same operation mode. If this
is not possible the unit that cannot operate in the higher operation
mode will change to hot standby. For more information see the chapter <xref href="Hot_Standby_CPT_0000358503.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="concept"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The table shows different examples of how the operation mode
priority functions in a redundant system.</p>
         <note class="- topic/note ">A dual system working
in parallel with a closed couple switch will function differently
since the redundancy is not ensured.</note>
